=head1 TEST PROCEDURE

=begin html
<PRE>
                    
       HA0    NUTX      R1      R2     CN0
        |       |       |       |       |
        | ====> | <-------------------- | 1.ICMP Echo Request
        |       |       |       |       |
        | <==== | --------------------> | 2.Home Test Init
        |       | --------------------> | 3.Care-of Test Init
        |       | <-------------------- | 4.Care-of Test
        | ====> | <-------------------- | 5.ICMP Error(Code=1)
        |       |       |       |       |
        | <==== | --------------------> | 6.ICMP Echo Reply
        |       |       |       |       |
        | ====> | <-------------------- | 7.ICMP Echo Request
        | <==== | --------------------> | 8.ICMP Echo Reply (*1)
        |       |       |       |       |
                    
        1. Send ICMP Echo Request. (out: HA0 -> NUTX, in: CN0 -> NUT0)
        2. Receive Home Test Init. (out: NUTX -> HA0, in: NUT0 -> CN0)
        3. Receive Care-of Test Init. (NUTX -> CN0)
        4. Send Care-of Test. (CN0 -> NUTX)
        5. Send ICMP Parameter Problem, Code 1. (out: HA0 -> NUTX, in: CN0 -> NUT0)
            # The Type field is set to 4(Parameter Problem).
            # The Code field is set to 1.
        6. Receive ICMP Echo Reply. (out: NUTX -> HA0, in: NUT0 -> CN0)
        7. Send ICMP Echo Request. (out: HA0 -> NUTX, in: CN0 -> NUT0)
        8. Receive ICMP Echo Reply. (out: NUTX -> HA0, in: NUT0 -> CN0)
                    
    Focus Packet Format:
        5. ICMP Parameter Problem
          o format #1
            IPv6 header
                source          = home agent
                destination     = care-of address
            ESP header
                SPI             = SA4 SPI (SA4 protects any header) or
                                = SA8 SPI (SA8 protects any header)
            IPv6 header
                source          = correspondent node
                destination     = home address
            ICMPv6 header
              ICMPv6 Error
                type            = 4 (Parameter Problem)
                code            = 1 (unrecognized Next Header type encountered)
                pointer         = 6 (The Next Header field of IPv6 header in HoTI)
                    
          o format #2
            IPv6 header
                source          = home agent
                destination     = care-of address
            IPv6 header
                source          = correspondent node
                destination     = home address
            ICMPv6 header
              ICMPv6 Error
                type            = 4 (Parameter Problem)
                code            = 1 (unrecognized Next Header type encountered)
                pointer         = 6 (The Next Header field of IPv6 header in HoTI)
                    
        7. ICMP Echo Request
          o format #1
            IPv6 header
                source          = home agent
                destination     = care-of address
            ESP header
                SPI             = SA4 SPI (SA4 protects any header) or
                                = SA8 SPI (SA8 protects any header)
            IPv6 header
                source          = correspondent node
                destination     = home address
            ICMPv6 header
              Echo Request
                    
          o format #2
            IPv6 header
                source          = home agent
                destination     = care-of address
            IPv6 header
                source          = correspondent node
                destination     = home address
            ICMPv6 header
              Echo Request
                    
        8. ICMP Echo Reply
          o format #1
            IPv6 header
                source          = care-of address
                destination     = home agent
            ESP header
                SPI             = SA3 SPI (SA3 protects any header) or
                                = SA7 SPI (SA7 protects any header)
            IPv6 header
                source          = home address
                destination     = correspondent node
            ICMPv6 header
              Echo Reply
                    
          o format #2
            IPv6 header
                source          = care-of address
                destination     = home agent
            IPv6 header
                source          = home address
                destination     = correspondent node
